    entry_requirements = '<div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>As a graduate of this degree, you can look forward to a broad range of exciting career opportunities in different sectors and industries. Below are some examples of the possible careers you can pursue with this degree:</p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<ul><li>Illustrator</li><li>Art director</li><li>Information designer</li><li>Interactive designer</li><li>Web designer</li><li>Design educator<br/>\n</li></ul>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>"The course at Western really challenged my thinking, and my ability to come up with ideas and be critical about my work. It definitely set me up for success in the future."<br/>\n<b style="\tfont-size: 1.0pc;\n"><br/>\n— Micah Williams, Bachelor of Design (Visual Communication)</b></p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>Applicants who have undertaken studies overseas may have to provide proof of proficiency in English. Local applicants who are applying through the Universities Admissions Centre (UAC) will find details of minimum English proficiency requirements and acceptable proof on the UAC website. Local applicants applying directly to the University should also use the information provided on the UAC website. <a href="https://www.uac.edu.au/undergraduate/courses/ws/720715.shtml" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><span>Find out more here. <i class="icomoon icon-external-link"></i></span><div class="sr-only"> Opens in new window</div></a></p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>Students are admitted on the basis of their ATAR score or equivalent.<br/>\n</p>\n</div><div class="component component--wysiwyg aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">\n<p>Wher